<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="574" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,659,1262]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,473,839,866]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">Diagnostic description.</emphasis>
Body laterally compressed, occasionally subcylindrical (
<taxonomicName box="[1112,1254,839,865]" family="Magnovidae" pageId="1" pageNumber="573" rank="family">Magnovidae</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1261,1371,839,866]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1261,1371,839,866]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">fam. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Antenna 1 accessory flagellum present.Antenna 2 peduncular article 1 not enlarged. Mandible molar strongly triturating of medium size or occasionally dominating mandible. Maxilliped inner plates well developed palp with 4 articles. Coxal gills on pereonite 2–6 or 2–7. Coxae 1–4 not ventrally acute. Coxae 1–3 well-developed, none hidden (except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas &amp; Barnard" authorityYear="1986" box="[151,326,983,1010]" class="Malacostraca" family="Megaluropidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Megaluropidae</taxonomicName>
). Gnathopod 1 smaller than or similar in size to gnathopod 2. Gnathopod 2 dactylus well-developed, large. Pereopods 3–7 none prehensile. Pereopod 4 coxa without posteroventral lobe (except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bousfield" authorityYear="1979" box="[1213,1432,1019,1045]" class="Malacostraca" family="Gammaroporeiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Gammaroporeiidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas &amp; Barnard" authorityYear="1986" box="[151,323,1055,1081]" class="Malacostraca" family="Megaluropidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Megaluropidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lowry &amp; Myers" authorityYear="2013" box="[334,475,1055,1082]" class="Malacostraca" family="Nuuanuidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nuuanuidae</taxonomicName>
). Pereopods 5–7 without rows of facial or marginal setae. Pereopod 7 subequal or longer than pereopod 5 (occasionally much longer than pereopod 5, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas &amp; Barnard" authorityYear="1986" box="[892,1067,1091,1118]" class="Malacostraca" family="Megaluropidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Megaluropidae</taxonomicName>
). Pereopod 7 similar in structure to pereopod 6. (except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas &amp; Barnard" authorityYear="1986" box="[409,584,1127,1154]" class="Malacostraca" family="Megaluropidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Megaluropidae</taxonomicName>
). Pleopods all well-developed. Epimera all well-developed. Urosomites 1–3 free. Uropods 1, 2 apices of rami with robust setae. Uropod 1 basofacial setae present or absent; without ventromedial spine. Uropod 3 biramous or occasionally uniramous. Telson laminar.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1223,1235,1262]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,659,1262]" box="[199,1223,1235,1262]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1236,1262]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">Remarks.</emphasis>
This set of characters separates the hadziidan amphipods from all other families.
</paragraph>
